<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 6:54PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Edgecombe and eastern Halifax Counties through 800 PM EDT...
At 654 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles west of Scotland Neck, or 13 miles northeast of Rocky Mount,
moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Tarboro, Halifax, Scotland Neck, Enfield, Whitakers, Hobgood, Speed,
Leggett and Tillery.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
